headline: Why The Story Around Ralph Lauren Is Evolving Amid Fresh Analyst Upgrades and Growth Cautions
summary: Ralph Lauren’s stock narrative has shifted in recent days, with analysts modestly increasing their fair value estimate from $354.11 to $365.87 per share. This reflects a cautiously optimistic outlook, fueled by strong brand momentum but tempered by concerns around growth sustainability.
